description.narrative: Output 2.1.4 Improved peace and stability and a lessening of ethnic tension in the conflict affected areas of Southern Kyrgyzstan through raising of living standards, increased employment opportunities and reduced frustration and alienation among the poorest children, youth and families in the Programme target areas, which contributes to Child Health, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Early Learning, Health Systems Strengthening, Learning And Child-Friendly Schools, Learning Outcomes, Maternal And Newborn Health, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Social Protection, Social Protection And Child Poverty, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes, Violence, Exploitation And Abuse, Wash In Schools And Ecd Centres. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 2.1 Equit. Access to Quality Services by 2016 with the focus on the most vulnerable groups in specifically targeted areas, more women, girls and boys have access to and use a continuum of integrated social services, including sanitation services
